## Summary of All Fixes

| # | Location | Bug | Fix |
|---|----------|-----|-----|
| 1 | `emitSyncFrom` | Failure path returned with stale `EXIT_NORMAL` | Now writes `EXIT_FALLBACK` to `g_exitReason[cpu]` before returning |
| 2 | `JitHelp_commit` | Rejected valid ROM addresses ≥ `0x80000000` | Removed bad-PC guard entirely; only ARM addresses matter |
| 3 | `emitCondSkip` | `cond==15` fell through into branch emission | Both 14 and 15 now return `SIZE_MAX` (unconditional) |
| 4 | `setC_xer` | XER.CA extraction was rewritten mid-function leaving code unreachable | Replaced with `setC_xer_clean()` — single coherent 3-instruction sequence |
| 5 | `primeCarry` (new) | ADC/SBC used `mtxer` directly from CPSR bits — XER format differs | Added `primeCarry()` using `addic r0, C, -1` to correctly set XER.CA from CPSR.C |
| 6 | `emitBX_SCR0` | Thumb-bit extraction into CPSR was garbled | Replaced with `emitBX_SCR0_correct()` — explicit extract+shift+clear+OR |
| 7 | `emitBlockXfer` | `bge` branch target pointed to wrong label | Rewrote branch structure with explicit forward-patch labels |
| 8 | `emitT_hiReg` | CMP (o==1) wrote result to `rd` instead of discarding | Result goes to temp `TA`/`TC`; flags set; `rd` unchanged |
| 9 | `validPC` (NDS) | Missing `0x08000000` cartridge ROM range | Added all real NDS memory regions including cart slot |
| 10 | `runCpu` | Compile failure path didn't track cycles | Added cycle accounting for all fallback paths |
| 11 | `runJitNds/Gba` | Fixed `CYCLES_PER_SLICE` instead of real cycles | Now accumulates per-instruction cycles, flushes once per call |
| 12 | `sLsrI`/`sAsrI` carry | Carry bit extracted at wrong shift amount | Fixed: `(32-i+1)&31` → rotates the right bit to position 31 |

