The fact that it alternates `r=0` then `r=1` every two cycles suggests the condition evaluation itself is wrong — the N flag is being computed incorrectly by the JIT. With `cpsr=800000DF`, N=1. If the branch at `02380024` is e.g. `BNE` and the comparison result is wrong, the branch will always fall back or always take the wrong path.

